mane.select.1: The MANE Select transcript is a single model chosen as a default choice for each human protein-coding gene that is representative of biology, well supported, expressed and highly conserved

The Matched Annotation from NCBI and EMBL-EBI is a collaboration between Ensembl/GENCODE and RefSeq. The MANE Select is a is a single model chosen as the default transcript for a human protein-coding gene. The MANE Select is considered to be the model which is best representative of the biology of the gene, according to metrics considering the level of supporting evidence, transcription expression, protein isoform conservation and knowledge of clinical variants. This transcript set matches GRCh38 and is 100% identical between RefSeq and Ensembl/GENCODE for 5' UTR, CDS, splicing and 3'UTR.

mane.plus_clinical.1: Transcripts in the MANE Plus Clinical set are additional transcripts per locus neccessary to support clinical variant reporting

Transcripts in the MANE Plus Clinical set are additional protein-coding transcripts considered necessary to complement the MANE Select model in a gene. For example transcripts containing known Pathogenic or Likely Pathogenic clinical variants not reportable using the MANE Select set. Note there may be additional clinically relevant transcripts in the wider RefSeq and Ensembl/GENCODE sets but not yet in MANE.
tsl.level_1.1: A transcript where all splice junctions are supported by at least one non-suspect mRNA.
tsl.level_2.1: A transcript where the best supporting mRNA is flagged as suspect or the support is from multiple ESTs
tsl.level_3.1: A transcript where the only support is from a single EST
tsl.level_4.1: A transcript where the best supporting EST is flagged as suspect
tsl.level_5.1: A transcript where no single transcript supports the model structure.
tsl.na.1: A transcript that was not analysed for TSL.
appris.principal1.1: Transcript model containing a protein isoform classified as PRINCIPAL:1 by APPRIS.

Transcript(s) expected to code for the main functional protein isoform based solely on the core modules in the APPRIS. Multiple PRINCIPAL:1 transcripts can be called in a gene due to alterative splicing within UTRs.
appris.principal2.1: Transcript model containing a protein isoform classified as PRINCIPAL:2 by APPRIS.

When the APPRIS modules cannot clearly select a single protein-coding isoform for a PRINCIPAL:1 transcript out of a pool of multiple candidates, a PRINCIPAL:2 model may instead be selected. This is model containing a protein isoform with a raw TRIFID score that is substantially higher than that for all other candidate models.
appris.principal3.1: Transcript model containing a protein isoform classified as PRINCIPAL:3 by APPRIS.

When the APPRIS modules cannot clearly select a single protein-coding isoform for a PRINCIPAL:1 or :2 transcript out of a pool of multiple candidates, a PRINCIPAL:3 model may instead be selected. This is model containing a protein isoform that has more proteomics support than other candidates.
appris.principal4.1: Transcript model containing a protein isoform classified as PRINCIPAL:4 by APPRIS.

When the APPRIS modules cannot clearly select a single protein-coding isoform for a PRINCIPAL:1, :2 or :3 transcript out of a pool of multiple candidates, a PRINCIPAL:4 model may instead be selected. This is model containing a protein isoform that has the highest raw TRIFID score compared with other candiates.
appris.principal5.1: Transcript model containing a protein isoform classified as PRINCIPAL:5 by APPRIS.

When the APPRIS modules cannot clearly select a single protein-coding isoform for a PRINCIPAL:1, :2, :3 or :4 transcript out of a pool of multiple candidates, a PRINCIPAL:5 model may instead be selected. This is model containing a protein isoform that has the longest CDS length compared with other candidates.
appris.alternative1.1: Transcript model containing a protein isoform classified as ALT1 by APPRIS.

For a gene in which the APPRIS core modules selected a PRINCIPAL:2, :3, :4 or : 5 model, an ALT1 is a candidate transcript model with a protein isoform that is conserved in at least three tested non-primate species.
appris.alternative2.1: Transcript model containing a protein isoform classified as ALT2 by APPRIS.

For genes in which the APPRIS core modules selected a PRINCIPAL:2, :3, :4 or : 5 model, an ALT2 is a candidate transcript model with a protein isoform that is not deemed to be conserved in at least three tested non-primate species.
gencode.gencode_basic.1: GENCODE basic is a subset of representative transcripts in the GENCODE geneset defined by length and completeness.

GENCODE Basic represents a subset of transcripts in the GENCODE gene annotation. For protein coding genes GENCODE Basic transcripts will only include full length transcripts with the 'protein coding' biotype that contain a complete CDS. For lncRNA genes, GENCODE Basic inlcudes the minimal set of transcripts that capture more than 85% of the introns at the locus. For other biotypes; pseudogene, sRNA and IG/TR the single transcript model at the locus will be tagged as GENCODE Basic.
canonical.ensembl_canonical.1: A single representative transcript chosen for each gene.

This transcript is the chosen canonical for its gene. For protein-coding genes, this is the MANE_Select transcript if there is one. If not, the canonical transcript is chosen by a pipeline that takes into account several criteria including transcript support (TSL), functional importance (APPRIS), representation in RefSeq and UniProt databases, length and coverage of pathogenic variants, where available. For non protein-coding genes, it is usually the transcript with the longest sequence and the same biotype as its parent gene.
